Kazanskoye Climate Summary

Located at an elevation of None meters (0 feet) above sea level, Kazanskoye has a Humid continental, no dry season, warm summer climate (Classification: Dfb). The district’s yearly temperature is 3.81ºC (38.86ºF) and it is -1.46% lower than Russia’s averages. Kazanskoye typically receives about 60.25 millimeters (2.37 inches) of precipitation and has 129.79 rainy days (35.56% of the time) annually.
